##I returned to Shenzhen from Wuhan before I sealed off the city. I volunteered to quarantine the community

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

It has been an extraordinary year, with some trepidation and some ups and downs. Back to Wuhan these days experience, like an adventure, in my mind engraved with a deep imprint.

Calm Wuhan

I returned to my hometown Wuhan from Shenzhen on January 20. I had engaged in the news work, also has many Wuhan Medical Circle Friend, therefore to Wuhan Pneumonia's matter has been paying close attention. From the earliest health experts to Wuhan, I have been closely tracking this matter. Because this year there is a big event at home, I must go back to Wuhan, also because the mother has been in Wuhan, the heart is very worried.

Originally, on January 17, I bought a high-speed train ticket for a family of four to return to Wuhan at 5 pm on the 20th. On the 18th and 19th, there was a significant increase in the release of information about pneumonia. The number of infections increased by more than 100 cases in two days. I have a bad feeling. Combined with some news from friends circle, the situation of pneumonia in Wuhan may be more than you think. After a day of hesitation, I decided to return the wife and children's tickets, a person back to Wuhan for the New Year.

On the evening of the 19th, after the ticket was refunded at Shenzhen East station, our small family had a reunion dinner at a nearby Hubei restaurant. When I went home, I thought, Wuhan epidemic is serious, whether it will be more serious later, SARS when I was in Wuhan University, those experiences vividly. At that time, masks, Banlangen and other supplies are out of stock. So the next morning I bought more masks in Shenzhen, Banlangen, Houttuynia, arhat fruit and other supplies, to his wife and children left A, back to Wuhan A.

At 4:00 in the afternoon, I went to the Shenzhen North Station wearing a mask. I found that there were still quite a few people wearing masks at the north station. Although only a few cases were confirmed in Shenzhen at that time, everyone's awareness of protection was still good, many people on the high-speed train also wear masks. The lady in the seat next to me saw me wearing a mask and pulled it out of my bag to put it on.

I was a little surprised by what I saw at the Wuhan high-speed Railway Station. I got off the bus at around 9 PM and went all the way from the hall to the Parking Lot. I was surprised to see few people wearing masks. I wonder in the heart, Wuhan people do so big heart? Aren't you afraid of pneumonia? The outbreak of awareness of the prevention of even worse than Shenzhen. We do not have a good sense of protection, I do not feel good, simply gave up the idea of taking public transport home. My home was on Paper Square Street in the centre of Jiangxia District, 35 km from the high-speed railway station, and I walked quickly out of the station hall to the roadside to hail an express train. After all, the express is normally cleaner than the taxi, with relatively few passengers. The driver wasn't wearing a mask. I barely spoke to the driver in the car. I kept my window open the whole time. I kept my mask on. I kept my hands in my pockets and tried not to touch the car. Got Home around 11:00 p.m.

On the way back, I talked about pneumonia through wechat and my friends in Wuhan, and the feedback made me gasp. A friend said, "should eat, drink, SARS Wuhan have experienced, afraid of a hammer, " and asked me to drink I was politely refused. There was also a video posted by a patient in a hospital with a Wuhan native accent, in which doctors at Huazhong University of Science and Technology were dressed in protective clothing, this guy actually said: "The situation is such a situation, several major issues, engage in this he people (frightening, Wuhan) . ".

I wonder, in the end is everyone for this pneumonia virus is very ignorant, or here's too inadequate publicity and guidance? There's a big question mark in my head. On the 20th I saw Wuhan, the Education City with the largest number of college students in the world and the largest transit city for people in mainland China, too calm in the face of pneumonia.

Midnight gallops, I must return to leave Wuhan

On the 21st, I spent a day at the paper mill, doing some work stuff online. Because did not buy the N95 mask, specifically asked to do related industries of friends and relatives can buy this mask. It was clear from the consultation process that everyone's awareness of vigilance and protection has not yet been tense up. You can always get a mask at the drugstore.

During the day when I go out, I wear a mask, also do not go to many places, also repeatedly told my mother as little as possible to go to many places. Brought back Houttuynia also asked my mother to boil water for the family to drink.

My father died in 2019. According to the custom in my hometown, on the first day of the New Year, all my relatives and friends will come to pay their respects. There will be five or six tables of guests. This is a big event for the countryside. On the morning of the 22nd, I prepared supplies and returned to the village with my mother and my brother's family.

In the three days from the 20th to the 22nd, News and information reports on pneumonia in Wuhan have increased significantly, and the number of reported cases has increased, including reports by academician Zhong Nanshan that pneumonia has infected people in the media. The case of pneumonia in Wuhan was immediately raised to a very high level within three days, three days up three levels, as if everyone had been awakened overnight by cold water. Then there are more videos coming out of hospitals, more videos and pictures of patients being picked up by ambulances, and more information on cases of infection or suspected infection around paper mills. Then there was the shortage of masks and alcohol in hospitals, and the number of people wearing masks increased, and the tension kept rising.

Back in the village, the atmosphere was much quieter. Tidied up the home, made a simple lunch, the afternoon in two uncle's home for dinner. Because there is no network, it is idle boring, and back with the cousin of the New Year in the village about Mahjong.

More than nine o'clock in the evening, my brother-in-law called me, said that now the situation is so serious, whether the first day of worship incense activities canceled. When an old person dies, it is a big deal to worship incense on the first day of the New Year in their hometown. Early in the morning on the first day of the New Year, people often go to the home of the deceased to worship incense on the first day. This is a bigger thing than new year worship. This is a very important and very serious custom. Suddenly they say they want to cancel it, i thought it was a bit abrupt, too, although I was wary of the severity of the outbreak. Afraid to make a decision, so I made a special call to uncle for his advice. Uncle hesitated a little, thinking about it, said: "Do not force who come, who do not come to understand, but can not cancel, incense or to worship. ". I also think uncle said quite reasonable, so told brother-in-law, he also accepted the advice.

Ten years did not return to the village for the New Year, we played cards and had a good time. (we played cards with a local doctor who was an acquaintance. We were all defensive.) After two o'clock in the evening, my sister called me again and told me, "Wuhan is closing down the city, we must hurry back! Now you can still buy tickets, or you may not be able to go. ".

Seal off the city? The news came as a bit of a shock to me. I knew it might be serious, but I never thought it would get to the point of closing the city in such a short time. I faltered for a moment, not knowing how to answer. Open the phone to see the news, confirmed the authenticity of the information. At 2:16 in the morning. My heart sank.

When my sister came back with both of her children, I understood her nervousness. But do we have to do the first day of worship? As the eldest son, I must bow to every one of the relatives and friends came to worship Incense, I left this matter how to do? What am I gonNA do about mom? Is it really that serious? If I don't go now, what's GonNa Happen? When can I go back to Shenzhen after years? If I can't go back for a long time, what will I do with two dolls in Shenzhen?

A series of question marks buzzed in my head, playing absent mindedly while my mind kept pondering, hoping to find a clear answer.

After thinking about it for more than half an hour, I finally came to my senses. If the government was able to make the decision to close down a mega city, a major transportation hub for more than 10 million people, it must have been because the epidemic was far more serious than anyone imagined. I don't want to get infected, so leaving Wuhan is a safer decision for me personally. Secondly, regarding the event of paying respects to Xiang, since the epidemic is so serious, from the point of view of everyone's health and safety, the emergency period cancelled the ceremony. I believe everyone should understand, so this burden can be laid down. Third, because I have two children to take care of in Shenzhen, the younger is only two years old, the older is in the first grade, if I can not go back for a month, the wife at home alone is difficult to deal with. Mom's safety problem can also be solved, take mom to go to Shenzhen together for New Year!

Suddenly, the game broke up, and I called my sister to tell her my decision. At that time, she had already been on the high-speed train back to Shenzhen at more than three o'clock. She was also told to call her mother first to do some thinking work, i think the old man should be hard to let go of these things at home, especially has prepared these hospitality materials. Hurried home, told her mother the seriousness of the matter, to go with her to Shenzhen, as I expected, she refused. Can Not put down incense worship, can not put down so many things at home, can not put down relatives and friends to visit new year, can not put down... all kinds of persuasion is really no way, but the Shenzhen home needs to take care of, not to mention the blockade in Wuhan for a long period of time not expected. In my understanding of the epidemic, a closure requires at least one incubation period, and a long one or even two incubation periods, which means it is possible to close for more than a month, a period that I simply can not afford. So I still have to go. So had to repeat mother, in the village on the New Year, do not return to the city, the city on the periphery of a few cases of the community, too unsafe. Mom took my advice, reassured me that I didn't have to worry about her, and let me go. With a heavy heart, I put on my backpack and went out. It's about 4:00 in the morning.

Cousin has been with me, see I decided to personally drive me to the Wuhan high-speed Railway Station fifty kilometers away. The first moment I got on the train I booked on my mobile phone the first high speed train ticket back to Shenzhen at 7:25. Due to the 12306 system, the ticket release information can not be updated until 6:00, and I am a little worried about the result of the high-speed railway station, after all, the decision to close the city has already happened, although it is 10:00 a.m. With an uneasy heart, at midnight gallop all the way to Wuhan high-speed Railway Station.

My cousin, on the way I fell asleep in the car, he has been driving, and I was cousin wake up when it is more than 5:40. The day has dawned. As I wasn't sure if I could release the tickets at six o'clock, but the train couldn't stay long when I got off at the second floor of the entrance to the station. My cousin said he would wait for me until I got the tickets and told him to return. Take me back if you can't get the tickets.

Everyone was wearing masks

Surprisingly, many people rushed to the high-speed railway station even though there were fewer people there than usual. After coming in, and I, straight to the front desk, asked whether today closed city can still buy tickets. Station officials told us they had not been notified. I think it's 10:00. To six o'clock to buy a ticket to refresh the APP, smoothly brush to the ticket, it was reassuring to call cousin to inform him to go home.

After swiping the ticket, I stood in front of the station for a few minutes, feeling very scared and unable to recover. What kind of days is this? What kind of epidemic is this? How many times in our lives can we ride this roller coaster? How many times can a city of 10 million people withstand such a shock? Is Tomorrow GonNA be okay here? When will it get better?

A photo was taken outside the station to mark the most memorable new year 2020 against the backdrop of the epidemic. The photos just left a few people in a hurry into the station's figure, their tension is so real. When I pulled into the station I looked out the window at the sky and again lost in thought.

After recovering from the spirit in the relatives and friends sent the first day of the cancellation of worship activities notice, at this moment everyone's life and safety is the most important, we can only break the stereotypes. I believe that my father in heaven must be the spirit of support and understanding. Sent a friend circle, to the friends reported under this thrilling situation.

Almost everyone in the waiting hall was wearing face masks, completely different from what they had seen three days earlier, and their faces were written with nervousness and trepidation.

While waiting in the ticket line, I chatted with several fellow passengers. "Did you book the train before or did you buy a ticket back to Shenzhen after seeing the news about the closure of the city? " Beyond my surprise, several people said they had watched the news about the closure of the city and caught the train back to Shenzhen. The lady behind me is evacuating her family from Wuhan. A young girl in the queue next door was obviously tired, "I was really upset, " she said. "I just drove to Wuhan with my brother just after 4:00. When I learned the news, my family didn't return, so I went straight to the high-speed railway station to buy a ticket back to Shenzhen. " Because I was worried about the epidemic and the impact of my work, she had to make that decision. After hearing what she said, I was surprised and helpless. I didn't know how to express it.

Just got on the train to smell a disinfection smell, the epidemic or told everyone to learn to prepare for and grow. Everyone was wearing a mask. The car was not full, from start to finish, I was sitting in seat F by the window, the seat next to me was always empty.

Go Wuhan! Go China!

On the car down, the uneasy heart is finally a little quiet down. I've got a lot on my mind, and I can't make sense of it. He sighed deeply and felt relieved. I left my mother alone in Wuhan. Was that selfish of me? The question crossed my mind. Although there are very good reasons, but I still dare not give a positive answer, because I really do not know what will happen after all.

While driving to the high-speed railway station, he called his brother and told him to evacuate. He hesitated to make a decision. I don't think he left. He had also returned with two small children, and it was certainly not safe for him to be in a city like this. Thought to call him, think about it, if he has decided to go, it is already on the way, if not gone, it should be in bed not to call.

Uncle called at seven o'clock and asked me if I had left. He asked me if the festival was cancelled. I think someone in the family saw my message in the family group and called him. I said it's too big a problem. Cancel it. He didn't take it all in. I said, uncle, you are over 70 years old. Have you ever seen such a big city as Wuhan shut down? He said, "No. ". I said that this is a serious problem, the epidemic is more serious than people think, or can not consider the old rules, people's safety is more important than anything, I'm sure you can understand. Uncle finally agreed with me.

Hang up the phone third uncle also called, is also to ask this matter, I convinced him again. The elderly have their own ideas, but this time can only say that the situation is too special, customs are important, but everyone's health and safety is more important, this is our social responsibility. For the father's "UNFILIAL" , do the son only later made up.

At 8 o'clock my brother-in-law called to inform me that he had arrived in Shenzhen and that I was on my way back. He was surprised and pleased. His company has dozens of employees, but also worried about the blockade too long out of the city, the company should do. The fact that his two sons are back together, in such great danger, is his biggest concern as a father. It may be selfish, but how can it be. Of course, we all know that we have been very careful about the outbreak, and our own chances of being infected are very low.

Did Not Sleep all night, looked at the mobile phone information also do not know when to fall asleep, a wake up to Guangzhou. The Sun is bright, the sky outside the window is so bright, finally saw the sun, feel more warmth and suddenly.

When I arrived in Shenzhen, I took a taxi straight home to avoid contact with more people, so I chose not to take the subway. Wearing a mask the whole time, I specifically told the driver I came back from Wuhan, the driver was surprised. Open the window and tell the driver we're not talking.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
■ I was isolated in my study at home.

Back home, the two babies to see me very happy. The son wanted to give me a hug, but his father was embarrassed. Tell my daughter to stay away from her father for a while and not to talk to me. Got Dressed, went straight to the bathroom to take a shower. I'm finally feeling a little relieved.

After the bath and my daughter rule three, these days do not get too close to me, do not go to my small room. Let the wife bought a disposable bowl chopsticks, tell her I want home isolation for half a month. Then made a report to the community grid, told him I returned from Wuhan, any need to cooperate with me.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
■ I set the temperature in my study to 28 degrees.

After I ate something, I went to my room to lie down. I want to sleep, but I can't stop looking at my phone. Seeing the comments on the Internet, I condemned those who left Wuhan before the city was closed. It made me question every choice I made. Isn't there a good reason for everyone to leave? I think everyone's life has some difficult to choose between the situation, if you determine that the risk of infection is very small, non-residents of Wuhan to return to their homes should be an acceptable choice. Of course, I dare not sing praises to myself, social responsibility education us, if oneself is infected that had better not go out to infect others. The question is, if we think we have a small chance of being infected, but the incubation period is about 10 days, how do we choose? This awkward situation, I am afraid that no matter how to give the standard right answer.

Back in the Shenzhen Circle, I can still feel the different working conditions in different places. In the information circle these days, we have seen that many infected people in Wuhan have been carried away from their homes. There are also many comments that many people have been infected and have not gone to the hospital, and the relevant authorities have not followed them at all, many people who are infected but can not be admitted to a hospital are again a source of walking infection. This made me feel even more why the epidemic was so out of control.

Relatively speaking, Shenzhen has done a good job in this respect. Community work is sinking, and it can clearly connect with and understand the situation of every person traveling from Wuhan or Hubei. This is extremely important for the control of the epidemic, at the very least, the government knows who this potential infection is and what its scope is. Of course, Wuhan and Shenzhen are not on the same level of difficulty.

It's New Year's Eve and only 15 minutes before the start of the new year. It was a night to remember, and a day to remember. Write these experiences, hoping to record this unusual disaster in the past, in the face of this disaster so that these superficial words have a little value, for a better tomorrow!
